Thai links Uighur militants to shrine blast | NWADG
By THOMAS FULLER and EDWARD WONG The New York Times
Posted: September 17, 2015 at 3:40 a.m.Updated: September 17, 2015 at 3:40 a.m.


 SAKCHAI LALIT
 
 
 Credit: AP

 Thai police chief Somyot Poompanmoung, shown in August, said Tuesday that the shrine bombing in Bangkok was retaliation in part for the dismantling of a human-trafficking network involving Uighurs. 


A month after the deadliest bombing in recent Thai history, Thailand's national police chief made his most explicit comments Tuesday about who carried out the attack and why.

